nsity we observed is less than at $\\sim$100 MHz.\nThese results suggest this pulsar is weaker and produces less frequent giant\npulses at 39 MHz than at 100 MHz.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Feb 2015 18:20:17 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 7 Feb 2015 23:50:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-10"}
