{"id":"1502.01434","submitter":"Miriam Farber","authors":"Miriam Farber and Alexander Postnikov","title":"Arrangements of equal minors in the positive Grassmannian","comments":"41 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We discuss arrangements of equal minors of totally positive matrices. More\nprecisely, we investigate the structure of equalities and inequalities between\nthe minors. We show that arrangements of equal minors of largest value are in\nbijection with sorted sets, which earlier appeared in the context of alcoved\npolytopes and Gr\\\"obner bases. Maximal arrangements of this form correspond to\nsimplices of the alcoved triangulation of the hypersimplex; and the number of\nsuch arrangements equals the Eulerian number. On the other hand, we prove in\nmany cases that arrangements of equal minors of smallest value are exactly\nweakly separated sets. Weakly separated sets, originally introduced by Leclerc\nand Zelevinsky, are closely related to the positive Grassmannian and the\nassociated cluster algebra. However, we also construct examples of arrangements\nof smallest minors which are not weakly separated using chain reactions of\nmutations of plabic graphs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Feb 2015 05:08:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-02-06"}
